## Frequently Asked Questions

### How long does anxiety therapy take to work?

The timeline depends on your anxiety disorder, symptoms, and treatment plan. Many people notice progress within several therapy sessions, especially with short term approaches like CBT. If response prevention or exposure-based work is involved, improvement often builds gradually as you practice skills between sessions.

### Can therapy address both stress and anxiety?

Yes. Therapy sessions often address stress and anxiety symptoms together because they can affect each other. Treatment may include coping skills, relaxation strategies, and ways to change unhelpful patterns. This can support stronger mental health and help you respond more calmly to everyday pressure.

